## 📥 Data Ingestion

### External Stage

Data files are stored in AWS S3 and accessed through Snowflake External Stages.

### Snowpipe

Automated ingestion using:

```text
PATIENT_PIPE
APPOINTMENT_PIPE
BILLING_PIPE
```

---

## 🗄️ RAW Layer

### Tables

```text
PATIENT_RAW
APPOINTMENT_RAW
BILLING_RAW
```

### Streams

```text
PATIENT_STREAM
APPOINTMENT_STREAM
BILLING_STREAM
```

Streams capture incremental changes and support Change Data Capture (CDC).

---

## 🔄 CORE Layer

### Core Tables

```text
PATIENT_CORE
APPOINTMENT_CORE
BILLING_CORE
```

### Exception Tables

```text
PATIENT_EXCEPTION
APPOINTMENT_EXCEPTION
BILLING_EXCEPTION
```

### Validation Rules

* Patient ID must not be NULL
* Appointment Date must be valid
* Billing Date must be valid
* Net Amount must be greater than or equal to zero
* Appointment Status must be:

  * Scheduled
  * Completed
  * No-Show
  * Cancelled

Invalid records are redirected to Exception Tables.

---

## 📊 MART Layer

### Dynamic Dimension Tables

```text
DIM_PATIENT
DIM_DOCTOR
```

### Dynamic Fact Tables

```text
FACT_APPOINTMENT
FACT_BILLING
```

Dynamic Tables automatically refresh and eliminate manual scheduling.

